@Node New " Nice ! "


    Version 1.0 was some kind of experimental... I did it for my private usage and them I thought it could be also usefull to other users.

    Soon I found that it wasn't very intuitive to use; A bit of reasoning : When someone gets a program that allows the AMIGA from booting with the WBStartup thing disabled, the first thing he/she does is to run the program (possibly with on the WBench opened) expecting a reboot from the computer, followed by the desired effect...
But it didn't worked that way - on version 1.0, You must 'Boot With No Startup-Sequence' on the Early Amiga Startup screen and then run NoWB from the AmigaDOS window. It simply wasn't "automatic" ...


    So, a complete re-write took place and Version 2.0 was born !!!.


        · Now everything is done automatically on booting by it. You just have
           to hold down the right mouse key until some color stripes appear
            on the screen, meaning that the WBStartup drawer is "disabled"

        · The old Shell mode usage from the 1.0 version is still available

        · There's no need to specify the seconds delay in order to get it
           working on slow HD's anymore !!! Due to a cleaver programming, 
            you can have the world's slower HD and use my program nicelly;
             Nice if booting from floppy (argh !)

        · The conflict with the PFS file system was "solved". On v1.0 it 
           seemed to unvalidate the boot partition if was run from a PFS
            boot partition ... I found it very strange, since NoWB only
             does OS legal stuff (read AmigaDOS commands ;)

            *Now* everything if working with PFS.

            @{B}BTW:@{UB} When testing v2.0 with PFS, I run again the v1.0 and this
            time I didn't got *no problems* ... NoWB1.0 behaved normally
            with PFS !  So I'm wondering if I really did a correct 
            installation of it by the time I tested with NoWB1.0 ...

            So 'Yeah !' for PFS and a big 'Booooooh !' for me %(
    
            
@EndNode

@Node What " Introduction"


      At last, version 2.0 is here !!! This time, a decent version 8)
      It's a lot more intuitive and safe to use than the previous version.


      NoWB allows you to boot your system without the loading of any programs in the 'WBStartup' drawer.  It's useful when you want to save memory and also load the WBench. See @{" this " link UFO}.

      I decided to do this, since every time I selected 'Boot With No Startup-Sequence' on the Early Amiga Startup screen and typed 'LoadWB' on the CLI, the OS load every program I had on the 'WBStartup' drawer as usual, which some of them asked for some stuff on the ENV: and T: devices (which are not mounted at this moment, of course 8) )

@EndNode

@Node req " Requirements "


    This program requires at least OS2.xx. Anyway, it would not be of any use to users of previous OS, since the WBStartup thing was only implemented on OS2.xx and above.

Also the DOS commands on C:

    - CPU      (see this @{" "link cpu})
    - Setpatch
    - Rename
    - Wait
    - LoadWB
    - Execute
@EndNode

@Node install " ... Although could be could be more simple ... "


    I didn't created any installer script, so you have to do it manually, sorry.


    So, get hold of you favourite file manager and do the following :

    · Copy the 'NoWB_AuxDir' drawer to your boot partition (the sys: volume)
    · Copy NoWB2 to C:
    · Now, edit your 'startup-sequence' by inserting the following anywhere
      *before* the C:LoadWB command; place it after C:SetPatch, as a suggestion:

           C:NoWB2 startup

      please note: the 'startup' argument is essential !!!
      »»»»»»»»»»»
    · Put the doc file anywhere you like, as long you can remember where 8)



    It's done !
@EndNode


