@Node Usage " How do I "


First words : *Don't* try to run 'nowb2_auxiliar_program'. This program is 
-----------   handled by NoWB2 only.


OK, let's go straigth to the point:


    NoWB2 may be used on two ways: Automatically on booting or manually on a Shell window.


      AUTOMATIC MODE
      »»»»»»»»»»»»»»

      It's what I call it when you decided to run it without having to type any command :

      This way, in order to run NoWB2 you just have to do a Reset on the AMIGA and keep holding the right mouse button until a set of color stripes appear on the screen, telling you that NoWB2 is activated. Now the system will load the Worbench and *none* of the undesirable WB programs...
      Don't forget to put the 'startup' argument ... Read @{" installation " link install }



      MANUAL MODE
      »»»»»»»»»»»»

      This is suited to do it if you're in a CLI/Shell window and *should not* be used if you already have the Wb loaded !!!

      On this mode, you have 2 more option :

         · Giving @{B} n@{UB}  as an argument, loads the Wb without executing 
           the s:user-startup.
         · Put an @{B} u@{UB}  if you don't want the s:user-startup thing ...

      Please note that, on the manual mode, an argument it's always needed; If you simply run NoWB2 with no args, it will show you the available arguments - It's a safety measure against some people that may try my program without reading the docs (running NoWB when the WorkBench is already loaded isn't the finest idea, you know)



PROBLEMS THAT MAY ARISE: 
-----------------------

  · NoWB writes on you HD (it does a bunch of Renames only), so it is wise to *always* wait for it to finish disk access before rebooting your computer (just look at the 'H. DISK' LED). If you do, you'll may get your boot partition unvalidated and corrupted, specially if you using the standard file system (FFS). So, be warned ...

    If this has happened, use some recovery program like 'ABTools' or 'DiskSalv4'.

  · When in 'AUTO MODE' (that is, if you hold the right mouse button during booting) it's advised to wait for the finishing of the whole process, even when you changed your mind about running this program and you do a Reset during booting... Anyway, if you did it by accident, NoBW2 has built in a 'doctor' who watch for all the required files and undoes any mistake caused by the Reset - Please note that if cannot revalidate you HD, if this happened ... It only take cares of the support files.

@EndNode

@Node bonus " Extra bytes "


      As a feature, each time NoWB is invoked, it executes a s:WB-startup file (if it exists) -> It was just a nice thing I decided to implement; Use it as you wish.
