@Node cpu " CPU stands for Central Processing Unit and every computer has one ! "


      The cpu command isn't directly related to the correct behavior of my program but i decided to use it as an extra when NoWB2 is invoked on a CLI/Shell window, after a 'Boot with no startup-sequence' action. 

      It seems that the cpu caches (if your processor have any) are not enabled during booting (although Setpatch does something on data caches, I think), so I decided to make NoWB2 enable those for you.
At least on @{"my system" link mysystem}, this flaw happens to occur ...


      @{B}A HINT :@{UB} put the following line on your s:startup-sequence

         c:cpu >nil: cache BURST DATACACHE DATABURST INSTCACHE INSTBURST

      This will enable all caches during normal startup boot.
@Endnode
